node.text: Morning walk at Tsutenkaku.
An old man is about to get into a local okonomiyaki restaurant. @kumagaaaai and i decide to go in too🤣
I was riding bicycle from Akihabara to Arakawa City, and I told myself to stop here for few seconds for this lovely view.
After two long years, here I come again, Shibuya. You are sexy and gorgeous as usual :D
World is so small. I bumped into an old friend here at the Glico sign area. He was there for a business trip while i was having a vacation.
4°C cold Osaka night looks warm.
Do you live to work or work to live? TGIF, time to stop working and relax!

Had a great time shooting with my man @kumagaaaai. We went to have a beer and awesome BBQ pork rice after a long-time standing in the cold weather. We were so cold and hungry but need to finish shooting our shots first.

I assume everyone would know this place already. In fact, I visited this place twice, first time was about three years ago, and the second time was a year ago. Last year was much crowded than three years ago, maybe because there are more tourists visit here. So I decided to come here at night, not as busy as the morning time, it’s all quiet, peaceful and calm. And most importantly, i got my shot.😎

Everyday life in Osaka. I really enjoy shooting Japanese people riding bicycle on the streets, it has its own unique cinematic feeling to it. Including myself, I bike whenever I visit Japan, with a very big backpack tho.

This is one of the typical “Instagram-angles” of Tautenkaku, do you agree with me? Representing I have visited Osaka without a doubt. Next time, I will share a night version of this angle 🤓🤓

今日工事 · Daily life in Tokyo ⚒
.
One thing I really admire Japan is that they always keep the construction area so clean and organized. They try to minimize the working space as small as possible and work very quietly so that people can still passing through without any panic. It is great to learn from this, attitude and discipline on work.
